  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water &amp; Sanitary Facilities for Ajegunle Slums</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This  project will provide  clean water and sanitary facilities for  a community in Ajegunle, Nigeria&apos;s most notorious slum.  Funds will support the construction of two boreholes and four blocks of modern latrines in Araromi, in Ajegunle; providing more than 5000 residents broader access to potable water and hygienic modern latrines.  The goal is to reduce incidences of  water, sanitation and hygiene-related diseases like cholera, typhoid and hepatitis among the very low income residents.</narrative>
  </description>
